    {
        "content": "<p>For Riccardo, unfortunately, not. <code>α</code> is the <code>SpecialLinearGroup K V</code> (for some finite dimensional <code>K</code>-vector space <code>V</code>), <code>deg</code> is the transvection degree, the minimal number required to write an element as a product of transvections, and <code>motive</code> is the assertion     <code>finrank K V ≤ deg e + finrank K e.fixedSubmodule</code>, where <code>e.fixedSubmodule</code> is the eigenspace for the eigenvalue <code>1</code>.</p>",
